{
  "page": "Harlan Tyrell",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\"><img alt=\"House Tyrell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/50px-House_Tyrell.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/75px-House_Tyrell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/100px-House_Tyrell.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Harlan Tyrell</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\"><img alt=\"House Tyrell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/50px-House_Tyrell.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/75px-House_Tyrell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/House_Tyrell.svg/100px-House_Tyrell.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Harlen.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Harlen.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c7/Harlen.png/300px-Harlen.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"387\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c7/Harlen.png/450px-Harlen.png 1.5x, /images/c/c7/Harlen.png 2x\" /></a><div>Harlan Tyrell as depicted in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <i>Histories &amp; Lore</i>.</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/High_Steward\" title=\"High Steward\">High Steward</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Highgarden\" title=\"Lord of Highgarden\">Lord of Highgarden</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Mander\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Mander\">Lord Paramount of the Mander</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Defender_of_the_Marches\" title=\"Defender of the Marches\">Defender of the Marches</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/High_Marshal_of_the_Reach\" title=\"High Marshal of the Reach\">High Marshal of the Reach</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_South\" title=\"Warden of the South\">Warden of the South</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Gardener\" title=\"House Gardener\">House Gardener</a> <small>(pre-Conquest)</small></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/5_AC\" title=\"5 AC\">5&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish desert</a> east of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hellholt\" title=\"Hellholt\">Hellholt</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Theo_Tyrell\" title=\"Theo Tyrell\">Theo Tyrell</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (appendix)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appendix)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appendix)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appendix)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Harlan Tyrell</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-harlen_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-harlen-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> was the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/High_Steward\" title=\"High Steward\">High Steward</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>. He was the first Tyrell to rule the Reach as <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Highgarden\" title=\"Lord of Highgarden\">Lord of Highgarden</a> after <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#The_Conquest\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Conquest</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#First_Dornish_War\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">First Dornish War</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Harlan Tyrell was a capable <a href=\"/index.php/Steward\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Steward\">steward</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>, serving <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> loyally.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Conquest\">The Conquest</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Conquest\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>At the time of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_before_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_2_Before_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years before Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">2&#160;BC</a>, Harlan Tyrell served as the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Steward\" title=\"High Steward\">High Steward</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Mern_IX_Gardener\" title=\"Mern IX Gardener\">Mern IX Gardener</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Reach\" title=\"King of the Reach\">King of the Reach</a>, an office his forebears had held for centuries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> After Mern died at the <a href=\"/index.php/Field_of_Fire\" title=\"Field of Fire\">Field of Fire</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> marched on <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a>, where Harlan yielded the castle without a fight, pledging his support to Aegon. For this, Aegon named him <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Highgarden\" title=\"Lord of Highgarden\">Lord of Highgarden</a> and gave him dominion over the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Mander\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Mander\">Lord Paramount of the Mander</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_South\" title=\"Warden of the South\">Warden of the South</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> despite the fact that the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">Tyrells</a> could only claim descent from <a href=\"/index.php/Garth_Greenhand\" title=\"Garth Greenhand\">Garth Greenhand</a> through the female line, while other houses, with older and more distinguished lineages, had closer blood ties to the now-extinct <a href=\"/index.php/House_Gardener\" title=\"House Gardener\">House Gardener</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harlan's elevation to Lord of Highgarden caused a number of his bannermen to voice their resentment, who bitterly complained about having to serve an \"upjumped steward\". However, their complaints were of no avail. Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a> speculates that Harlan had been chosen as the new Lord of Highgarden by Aegon I because the Tyrells had not taken up arms against the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryens</a>, whereas the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Oakheart\" title=\"House Oakheart\">Oakhearts</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Florent\" title=\"House Florent\">Florents</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Rowan\" title=\"House Rowan\">Rowans</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">Peakes</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Redwyne\" title=\"House Redwyne\">Redwynes</a> had marched beside King Mern.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"First_Dornish_War\">First Dornish War</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: First Dornish War\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Harlan served the Targaryens loyally and proved able in his lordship of the Reach. During the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Dornish_War\" title=\"First Dornish War\">First Dornish War</a>, he marched south in <a href=\"/index.php/4_AC\" title=\"4 AC\">4&#160;AC</a> beside King Aegon at the head of a massive army thirty thousand strong, led by two thousand mounted <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> and three hundred <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">bannermen</a>. Lord Tyrell was heard to say that they had the strength to smash any Dornish army that tried to oppose them, even without Aegon and his <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion\" title=\"Balerion\">Balerion</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The king and Lord Tyrell warred against the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornish</a> mountain lords in the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince%27s_Pass\" title=\"Prince&#39;s Pass\">Prince's Pass</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> however the Dornishmen never gave proper battle, withdrawing upon sight of the invading host. Upon emerging from the Prince's Pass, Aegon divided his forces and marched against <a href=\"/index.php/Skyreach\" title=\"Skyreach\">Skyreach</a>, while Harlan was sent south against Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Uthor_Uller\" title=\"Uthor Uller\">Uthor Uller</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hellholt\" title=\"Hellholt\">Hellholt</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Dornish sun proved unrelenting to the invaders as Lord Tyrell marched towards the Hellholt, with his men struggling to find water as every waterhole and oasis in the army's path had been poisoned. Horses began to die daily, followed by their riders; Harlan lost a quarter of his men and nearly all his horses to the Dornish sands. By the time the Tyrell army had arrived at the Hellholt, he founded it abandoned,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> the Ullers having fled.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the Targaryens had claimed <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a>, Harlan was placed in charge of putting down revolts, while Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Rosby\" title=\"Jon Rosby\">Jon Rosby</a> was given charge of Sunspear. The king had thought the Hellholt was well situated to deal with any revolts. However, the Tyrell men sickened from the sulphurous waters of the <a href=\"/index.php/Brimstone\" title=\"Brimstone\">Brimstone</a>, while Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vaith\" title=\"House Vaith\">Vaith</a> and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Qorgyle\" title=\"House Qorgyle\">Qorgyle</a> had their spearmen cut down Tyrell foraging parties and patrols. In <a href=\"/index.php/5_AC\" title=\"5 AC\">5&#160;AC</a>, upon learning of <a href=\"/index.php/Defenestration_of_Sunspear\" title=\"Defenestration of Sunspear\">the fall</a> of Sunspear and Lord Rosby's death at the hands of Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Meria_Martell\" title=\"Meria Martell\">Meria Martell</a>, Harlan gathered his remaining strength and announced his intentions to capture <a href=\"/index.php/Vaith\" title=\"Vaith\">Vaith</a> and retake Sunspear. However, he vanished with his entire army in the sands of Dorne east of the Hellholt, never to be found again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harlan was succeeded in his titles by his young son <a href=\"/index.php/Theo_Tyrell\" title=\"Theo Tyrell\">Theo</a>, who was much reluctant to continue the war against Dorne following the fate that befell his father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Harlan's name is misspelled as \"Harlen\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-harlen_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-harlen-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> in the appendices of <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harlan_Tyrell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\"